# Static Website Deployment with Terraform and AWS S3

This project demonstrates how to deploy a static website to AWS S3 using Terraform. The infrastructure includes an S3 bucket configured for website hosting, bucket policies for public access, and uploads of your static website files.

---

## Infrastructure Overview

- Creates an S3 bucket with static website hosting enabled.
- Configures the bucket to allow public read access for website content.
- Uploads `index.html` and `error.html` files to the S3 bucket.
- Sets bucket policy to enable public access to the website files.

---

## Prerequisites

- AWS CLI installed and configured with credentials that have permission to manage S3 and IAM resources.
- Terraform installed (v1.x or higher recommended).
- Your static website files (`index.html` and `error.html`) ready.

---

